data.text:
Football

Victoria University of Wellington Association Football Club (VUWAFC) is the largest senior football club in Wellington.

VUWAFC is also the only football club located in Central Wellington. The club's main home ground is Boyd Wilson Field (turf at Kelburn campus) while other home matches are also played at Kelburn Park (beneath the cable car) and Anderson Park (in the Botanical Gardens).

Originally founded in 1943, the club now has 21 senior teams, including 4 women's teams. Teams play on weekends during the winter season which runs between April and August each year. The club has more than 300 members and plenty of social events to keep you interested throughout the season!

If you'd like to get involved with any of our teams, send an email. We have competitive and social teams to suit all abilities and ages. All teams play in local leagues around the Wellington area.

Check our Wikipedia page.
